  "body": "**Description**\r\nWhen ~ symbol used in path variables it have to refer to home directory, but causes error\r\n\r\n**Steps to Reproduce**\r\nIn order to replicate the behavior, please provide a detailed list of steps:\r\n1. Set `Init.ChainSpecPath=\"~/chain.json\"` or any other path variable\r\n2. Run and see something like:\r\n` System.IO.FileNotFoundException: Chainspec file does not exist /folder/[...]/~/chain.json`\r\n\r\n**Actual behavior**\r\nFile not found error\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\nShould correctly read chainspec from /home/username/chain.json\r\n\r\n**Desktop (please complete the following information):**\r\nPlease provide the following information regarding your setup:\r\n - Operating System: Ubuntu\r\n - Version: 20.04\r\n",
